node.text:
Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Push the right-hand crown of the incredible BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon and the engine comes to life – the crankshaft turns and the 16 pistons pump up and down, just like BUGATTI’S iconic W16 engine. Two “turbochargers” on the side of the engine block spin while the engine runs, adding to the visual impact.
Incredible to see and unbelievably complicated to realize (the movement is comprised of 578 components), the BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon timepiece seamlessly marries engines and watches – something no other watchmaker has done before.

The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

In the world of watchmaking, the presence of a tourbillon in a watch’s movement places the piece among the elite. @JacobandCo’s Twin Turbo Furious 300+ sets itself apart from this rarified group, incorporating two accelerated triple axis tourbillons into its striking design. The tourbillons work to compensate for the effects of gravity on the precision of the movement.⠀ ⠀
⠀
Even the case of the Twin Turbo Furious Bugatti 300+ is super complicated – made of forged carbon, with a titanium core to ensure water resistance - the case alone is comprised of 88 parts. The grand complication movement is made up of 832 individual parts – incredible to consider that many parts coming together, and amazing to see in action.⠀

node.text: @simuliu wore the Astronomia Solar Baguette Jewelry Planets Zodiac during his during his breakout appearance at the Met Gala Monday, a watch that represents a beautifully artistic, highly refined, and fully mechanical recreation of our solar system. In constant movement, the upper platform completes a clockwise rotation every ten minutes, while simultaneously driving the diamond-set and planetary base dial in a counterclockwise rotation in ten minutes to add further animation and complexity to this unique take on celestial watchmaking. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #metgala #StarsInJacobandCo

node.text: @simuliu is basking in the glow of Monday’s Met Gala, where his appearance wearing the Astronomia Solar Baguette Jewelry Planets Zodiac lit up social media. The 44mm 18k white gold and sapphire case reveals three colorful sphere-shaped gems representing planets and one yellow sapphire as the sun all featuring the exclusive Jacob-cut of 288 carats. The blue PVD dial displays zodiac signs that are hand-engraved and filled with 18K rose gold. This celestial scene floats over a base of baguette diamonds. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #metgala

node.text: The breakout star of the 2021 Met Gala was @simuliu, who plays the lead character of the 2021 Marvel film, “Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings.” Liu walked the red carpet sporting the Jacob & Co. node.text: The film, Scarface, has been etched in our cultural consciousness since its release in 1983. Jacob & Co. honors this movie with the groundbreaking Opera Scarface Rose Gold watch. It integrates the movie’s theme music, a plaque of the famous poster and even the iconic inscription, “The World is Yours.” It’s combined with high watchmaking innovations such as a triple-axis tourbillon, a two-cylinder music box and a movement made of 658 components. There has never been a watch like the Opera Scarface. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie #scarface

node.text: Al Pacino’s iconic portrayal of Tony Montana, in “Scarface,” has been recreated with the Opera Scarface watch. It contains all the imagery and sounds from the 1983 film. A two-cylinder music box plays the theme song, “Bolivia,” when Montana visits the cocaine kingpin there. "The World is Yours" 18K Rose Gold and red lacquered Globe in the center of the dial serves as the symbol of his violent death. The world was his and now it can be yours with the Opera Scarface. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorology #scarface

node.text: In an exclusive partnership with NBC/Universal, Jacob & Co. honors the movie, Scarface, with the groundbreaking Opera Scarface Rose Gold, which integrates symbols and sounds from the iconic crime drama into a masterpiece of high horology. A pusher at 10 o'clock on the 18k gold and sapphire crystal case activates the 120-note music box that plays the “Bolivia” song from the movie while the entire dial rotates 120 degrees. These functions along with a triple-axis tourbillon and the time display are powered by the Manual-Winding JCFM04 movement comprised of 658 parts. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie #scarface

node.text: 💎 Introducing 💎 The Astronomia Everest Black Gold is a watch created by Jacob & Co. in collaboration with Swedish explorer and environmental activist, @johanernst. Inside the 47mm black gold and sapphire case and nestled within the iconic Astronomia movement, are details that symbolize significant moments from Nilson’s 27 years of adventures. They include a rock from Mount Everest mounted on the top of the movement and two glass containers of water collected by Nilson from the North and South Poles.
